{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Workout Tracker","technologies":"ReactJS (with Router, Redux and axios), JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3","priority":1,"slug":"workoutTracker","shortDesc":"My first real-world React app created to help with my gym workouts.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png","srcSet":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/a0798/horizontal.png 180w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/83f67/horizontal.png 360w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png 720w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/728bb/horizontal.png 1080w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/2513a/horizontal.png 1440w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/ec873/horizontal.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>First React app that I designed built from scratch (completely on my own). Its purpose is to log workouts. After creating a routine, it is very easy to log exercises and modify them on the fly. Features very clear interface, stores data offline on localStorage.</p>\n<p>Youtube demo: <a href=\"https://youtube.com\">https://youtube.com</a></p>\n<p>Github repo: <a href=\"https://github.com\">https://github.com</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Tablet Dashboard legacy","technologies":"HTML5, CSS3 (display: grid), JavaScript (with jQuery)","priority":2,"slug":"tabletDashboardLegacy","shortDesc":"Basic dashboard for my smart home project. Legacy, because I am in the process of rewriting it as a React app.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/6fbf7/TabletDashboardLegacy.png","srcSet":"/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/a0798/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 180w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/83f67/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 360w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/6fbf7/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 720w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/728bb/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1080w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/2513a/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1440w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/ec873/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 200px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"altText\"\n        title=\"altText\"\n        src=\"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/9ec3c/horizontal.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/bc08f/horizontal.png 50w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/c0399/horizontal.png 100w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/9ec3c/horizontal.png 200w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/135ae/horizontal.png 300w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/c7805/horizontal.png 400w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/a987b/horizontal.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n \n </p>\n<p>Tablet Dashboard Legacy is a dashboard for my custom smart home system. Displays current time, date, weather, forecast. Connects to Google's APIs to download Google Calendar. Shows data from smart home sensors (MQTT through WebSockets). Can open main and small gate, plays an audio alert on entrance. Features automatic night and silent mode.</p>\n<p><strong>Written in legacy Javascript, when I didn't have much knowledge or experience - code is not optimal by any means (and looks ugly).</strong> Uses CSS3 grid display, ES5 JS, bits of jQuery.</p>\n<p>Youtube demo: <a href=\"https://youtube.com\">https://youtube.com</a></p>\n<p>Github repo: <a href=\"https://github.com\">https://github.com</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Personal website - portfolio","technologies":"React, Gatsby, ES6 JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3","priority":2,"slug":"personalWebsite","shortDesc":"This portfolio","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/6fbf7/Portfolio2.png","srcSet":"/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/a0798/Portfolio2.png 180w,\n/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/83f67/Portfolio2.png 360w,\n/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/6fbf7/Portfolio2.png 720w,\n/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/728bb/Portfolio2.png 1080w,\n/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/2513a/Portfolio2.png 1440w,\n/static/29bdb0f109d82c069da494faf366b60e/ec873/Portfolio2.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>Tablet Dashboard Legacy is a dashboard for my custom smart home system. Displays current time, date, weather, forecast. Connects to Google's APIs to download Google Calendar. Shows data from smart home sensors (MQTT through WebSockets). Can open main and small gate, plays an audio alert on entrance. Features automatic night and silent mode.</p>\n<p><strong>Written in legacy Javascript, when I didn't have much knowledge or experience - code is not optimal by any means (and looks ugly).</strong> Uses CSS3 grid display, ES5 JS, bits of jQuery.</p>\n<p>Youtube demo: <a href=\"https://youtube.com\">https://youtube.com</a></p>\n<p>Github repo: <a href=\"https://github.com\">https://github.com</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Tablet Dashboard","technologies":"ReactJS, JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3","priority":3,"slug":"tabletDashboardNew","shortDesc":"Tablet Dashboard remade as a React app.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png","srcSet":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/a0798/horizontal.png 180w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/83f67/horizontal.png 360w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png 720w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/728bb/horizontal.png 1080w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/2513a/horizontal.png 1440w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/ec873/horizontal.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>Tablet Dashboard remade as a React app. Very similiar in user interface, backend completely different.</p>\n<p>Youtube demo: <a href=\"https://youtube.com\">https://youtube.com</a></p>\n<p>Github repo: <a href=\"https://github.com\">https://github.com</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Burger Builder","technologies":"ReactJS (with Router, Redux and axios), JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3","priority":4,"slug":"burgerBuilder","shortDesc":"Burger Builder app created during a comprehensive online React course.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png","srcSet":"/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/a0798/horizontal.png 180w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/83f67/horizontal.png 360w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/6fbf7/horizontal.png 720w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/728bb/horizontal.png 1080w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/2513a/horizontal.png 1440w,\n/static/4a965b3905c2cdceb7c10e9b2d99f163/ec873/horizontal.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>A burger builder app i made during a course <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/course/react-the-complete-guide-incl-redux/\">React - The Complete Guide</a> (Maximillian Schwarzmuller, udemy.com). Started with a simple app, over time built into an advanced webapp. Features authentication, Redux for global state keeping, axios for storing data in database.</p>\n<p>Youtube demo: <a href=\"https://youtube.com\">https://youtube.com</a></p>\n<p>Github repo: <a href=\"https://github.com\">https://github.com</a></p>"}}]}}}